    Retrieve Dataset Information

    infoDataSet.Rd

    This function extracts information from a dataset object, typically from a file like "datasets-hpmlk.csv". It returns various attributes related to the dataset.

    infoDataSet(dataset)

    Arguments

    dataset

    A dataframe or list containing dataset attributes.

    Value

    A list with the extracted dataset attributes, including:

    id

    Dataset ID

    name

    Dataset name

    instances

    Number of instances

    inputs

    Number of input attributes

    labels

    Number of labels

    LabelsSets

    Label sets information

    single

    Single-label classification indicator

    maxfreq

    Maximum frequency of labels

    card

    Cardinality of the dataset

    dens

    Density of the dataset

    mean

    Mean value of dataset attributes

    scumble

    Scumble measure

    tcs

    TCS value (Label co-occurrence complexity)

    attStart

    Starting index of attributes

    attEnd

    Ending index of attributes

    labStart

    Starting index of labels

    labEnd

    Ending index of labels

    distinct

    Number of distinct values

    xn, yn, gridn, xt, yt, gridt

    Grid-related attributes

    Examples

    dataset <- data.frame(ID = 1, Name = "SampleData", Instances = 100, Inputs = 10, Labels = 5)
info <- infoDataSet(dataset)
print(info$name)  # Output: "SampleData"
#> [1] "SampleData"
